summary: This document is a template or guide from T-Mobile explaining the structure and interpretation of subscriber information reports provided in response to law enforcement requests. It details the various data fields included (subscriber, account, device, billing details) and lists contact information for wholesale/MVNO partners where T-Mobile does not possess subscriber data.
keyFacts: The document is a guide for interpreting T-Mobile subscriber data provided to law enforcement, indicating such records were part of the investigation.
It details extensive personal data fields available, including name, address, SSN, birth date, device identifiers (ICCID, IMSI, IMEI), and call details.
The document lists numerous Mobile Virtual Network Operators (MVNOs) and wholesale partners, providing their legal compliance contact information for separate subpoena requests.
It explains that a target may generate multiple subscriber files if they used multiple devices or had service suspensions within the investigation timeframe.
The document itself contains no specific subscriber data, names, or events related to the Epstein case; it is a procedural template.
